It's time to destroy our bedroom. The last room in the house where nothing has been done except a little decorating.
The ugly electric fireplace and the hearth must go. We need to rebuild the fireplace, replace the chipped plaster and smooth it out. Then build a custom closet.
We always start with a rough pencil sketch…
The dirty part of the job is done.
At the back of the chimney, we found a few dead birds, very dry :(
Everything ready for the plasterer next week
The small side niche has turned out well
Here comes a new wardrobe in (but we haven't even started with the design yet 🙈)
Oh, look what we found behind the heater!
And we even thought of installing this nice little air vent, so the chimney doesn't get damp
The chimney sweep has installed the cover and the cap. Now it should be a bit safer for the crows that like to nest up there🪺
The plasterer is done. Tomorrow the floor will be laid!
The cork underlay is in place, I have made a toilet paper roll sawdust extractor for the vacuum cleaner 😂
Parts for the floor are ready and can be laid. We are currently having a tea break
Buhu. Today we are making slow progress, because of super complicated cuts around the door posts, so that we can have a smooth transition to the hallway (where the floor will also be relaid). @user45@twitter.com has cursed me
Done, but at the end! The crowning achievement was the terrible assembly instructions for the new bed. Tonight we will sleep well!
The floor in the hallway and all the baseboards are still missing. The decorator will come in a month, so we currently have a raw plaster look
A bit more DIY work in the evening to cut or chisel the lower sections around the doorposts where the floor will then fit seamlessly underneath.
The cork underlay is now also in the hallway.
Yesterday we finished the floor in the hallway! Then out at 5 a.m. to pick up item 1 at Heathrow, then a nap and final sprint in the hallway, the boards are installed. The joints will be made once the adhesive is dry
